Use Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF). Score each result from both methods then combine:

```ts
function rrf(bm25Ranks: Map<string, number>, knnRanks: Map<string, number>, k=60) {
  const scores = new Map<string, number>();
  for (const [id, rank] of bm25Ranks) scores.set(id, (scores.get(id)??0) + 1/(k+rank));
  for (const [id, rank] of knnRanks)  scores.set(id, (scores.get(id)??0) + 1/(k+rank));
  return [...scores.entries()].sort((a,b) => b[1]-a[1]);
}
```

RRF is robust because it only uses rank positions, not raw scores.
